## Standalone Agent Usage (outside the workflow)

The stepped workflow above governs **artifact generation** only. The following agents can be invoked **independently at any time**, at any step, without advancing the workflow:

| Agent | How to invoke | When to use |
|-------|--------------|-------------|
| [`technical_analyst`](../agents/technical_analyst.md) | `@.cursor/agents/technical_analyst.md` | Before or after any step — assess feasibility, complexity, and risks for the current artifacts |
| [`technical-devils-advocate`](../agents/technical-devils-advocate.md) | `@.cursor/agents/technical-devils-advocate.md` | Before or after any step — challenge assumptions, surface edge cases, stress-test the current artifacts |
| [`doc_review_assistant`](../agents/doc_review_assistant.md) | `@.cursor/agents/doc_review_assistant.md` | After implementation — verify PRs against acceptance criteria, generate release notes |
| [`backlog_architect`](../agents/backlog_architect.md) | `@.cursor/agents/backlog_architect.md` | Directly, if you already have a confirmed spec and want to skip Step 1 |

**Rules for standalone usage:**
- When you `@`-mention an agent directly, that agent runs — the workflow does NOT block it.
- Standalone agent output does not advance the workflow step. For example, running `technical_analyst` after Step 1 does not move you to Step 2.
- You can run multiple standalone agents between steps (e.g. run both `technical_analyst` and `technical-devils-advocate` after Step 1 before confirming to proceed to Step 2).
- If you don't want to use the stepped workflow at all, simply invoke agents directly by `@`-mentioning them. The workflow gates only activate when the agent is generating SDD artifacts (feature specs, stories, plans) without a specific agent being invoked.

---

## Anti-Patterns

- Generating stories in the same response as the feature spec
- Generating a plan before stories are reviewed
- Generating Jira/Confluence artifacts without being asked
- Assuming the user wants all steps because they gave a detailed prompt
- Writing files outside the configured output directory
- Blocking a standalone agent invocation because "the workflow hasn't reached that step"
